<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-494-872  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 494 872.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  July 1990 v7 n7 p201(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>McGee; The Playroom; Preschool Pack. (Software Review) (Macintosheducational software for preschoolers) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Beekman, George; Holmes, Jeanne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Three educational software programmers for pre-schoolers arereviewed: Lawrence Productions' $39.95 McGee; BroderbundSoftware's $69.95 The Playroom; and Nordic Software's $69.96Preschool Pack.andP;  McGee is an interactive picture story designedfor 2- to 4-year olds.andP;  It is initially delightful, but mostchildren lose interest after exploring all of the 'rooms' in theprogram.andP;  Preschool Pack offers color graphics on Mac IIs andcombines many diverse games and activities.andP;  The program has acustomization mechanism for creating 'learning cycles.' ThePlayroom includes a variety of responsive and games and toys thatcan keep children interested for some time.andP;  Its major drawback isa key-disk copy protection scheme that makes it unworkable on theMac IIci.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lawrence Productions Inc. (products)Broderbund Software Inc. (products)Nordic Software (products).andO;Product:   McGee (Educational software)The Playroom (Educational software)Preschool Pack (Educational software).andO;Topic:     Educational softwareEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>